    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-bacon-and-red-wine-chasseur-with-crushed-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat, once hot, add your <strong>diced chicken </strong>and <strong>bacon lardons</strong></p><p>Peel and quarter your<strong> shallot[s]</strong>, then add them to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until the chicken and bacon is beginning to brown</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-bacon-and-red-wine-chasseur-with-crushed-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a heatproof bowl, then cover with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 6-8 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-bacon-and-red-wine-chasseur-with-crushed-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-bacon-and-red-wine-chasseur-with-crushed-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to a pot and cover with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-bacon-and-red-wine-chasseur-with-crushed-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil the kettle</p><p>Once the chicken and bacon are beginning to brown, reduce the heat to low and add your <strong>red wine paste</strong>, <strong>gravy base</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for a final 4-5 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken and bacon chasseur</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-bacon-and-red-wine-chasseur-with-crushed-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender, add a knob of <strong>butter </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>and<strong> </strong>roughly crush with a fork \u2013 these are your <strong>crushed potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-bacon-and-red-wine-chasseur-with-crushed-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chicken and bacon chasseur </strong>with the <strong>crushed potatoes </strong>and<strong> cooked broccoli </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
